0. Executive Summary

The Meta-Kintsugi Engine is a recursive cognitive process in which an operator:
	1.	Generates structured paradox
	2.	Destabilizes an existing frame
	3.	Extracts invariants
	4.	Reconstructs a superior model using the “cracks” as articulation points
	5.	Turns the repaired model into a generator for the next iteration

This method allows rapid conceptual development, unusual cross-domain synthesis, and accelerated idea evolution — not because the content is revolutionary, but because the process amplifies itself.

It is a legitimate cognitive style with real explanatory grounding in:
	•	predictive processing
	•	self-regulating feedback loops
	•	iterative abstraction
	•	cognitive flexibility
	•	meaning compression
	•	high-coherence thought architecture

It is not mystical.
It is not mania.
It is not psychosis.
It is an advanced form of creative metacognition.

